7_SAS_On Cloud Models What is Public Cloud.


Q1
How many types of cloud models are there?
ANS
3 - PUBLIC, PRIVATE, HYBRID
Q2
What are public clouds?
ANS
OWNED, OPERATED, MAINTAINED BY C.S.P. (AWS, MICROSOFT AZURE, GCP)

CLOUD COMPUTING ENVIRONMENTS OWNED AND OPERATED BY THIRD-PARTY SERVICE PROVIDERS.
Q3
Services provided by cloud service providers users can save money because they are sharing resources and services with other cloud users over the internet? True/False.
ANS
TRUE - SHARED INFRA, COST SHARING, PAYG MODEL, RESOURCE ALLOCATION EFFICIENCY.
Q4
When using the cloud services from cloud service providers who maintains the hardware if anything happens?
ANS
THE C.S.P.
Q5
What are some examples of public cloud service providers?
ANS
AWS, MICROSOFT, GOOGLE, IBM, ALIBABA
Q6
What are some examples of companies that use public clouds?
ANS
UBER, NOVARTIS, SMALL AND MEDIUM BUSINESS COMPANIES AS WELL THAT USE CLOUD TO SAVE COSTS AND GET THE BENEFITS THE CLOUD PROVIDER PROVIDES.
Q7
Public clouds are used by both small and large companies? True/False.
ANS
TRUE
Q8
When cloud users share computing resources to save cost it is called ________?
ANS
MULTI TENANCY
Q9
Is it easy to build the hardware compared to using the hardware provided in public clouds? True/False.
ANS
FALSE
Q10
Why is it cheaper to use cloud service from cloud service providers like AWS?
ANS
MULTI TENANCY, REDUCTION OF CAPEX, FOCUS ON GOALS OF BUSINESS AND NOT WORRY ABOUT INFRASTRUCTURE COSTS AND OTHER COSTS.

PAY AS YOU GO, SCALABILITY OF RESOURCES (NO UNDERUTILIZATION, NO IDLE RESOURCES)

ECONOMIES OF SCALE, PAY AS YOU GO, SCALABILITY AND FLEXIBILITY, NO MAINTENANCE COSTS, REDUCED OPERATIONAL OVERHEAD, ACCESS TO ADVANCED TECHNOLOGIES


